<h2 class="learn-heading">Learn: Loose Leash Walking vs "Heel"</h2>

<p class="mb-4"><strong>Loose leash walking</strong> is not a "heel." A loose leash walking dog is walking at your side and the leash is in a relaxed J-shape but they have some freedom. They can sniff things, look around, and enjoy the walk. The key rule is: the leash can never go tight.</p>

<p class="mb-4">A <strong>heel</strong> is much more precise. The dog's shoulder is aligned with your leg and their attention is fully on you. We'll get to this in advanced training, but for now loose leash walking is the goal.</p>

