</div>

<div class="exercise-section">
  <h3>Exercise: Erratic/Unpredictable Walking</h3>

  <p>Now we extend how far you can walk with a loose leash before rewarding. Mix it up!</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Start by rewarding every 10 steps of loose leash walking</li>
    <li>Gradually extend to 20 steps, then 30, then 50</li>
    <li>Mix it up - sometimes reward at 10 steps, sometimes at 40</li>
    <li>Always reward at corners and after distractions</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h2 class="learn-heading">Learn: Two-Mississippi Pop</h2>

<p>If you absolutely feel the need to correct, here's the tool for the job. It's called a <strong>Two-Mississippi Pop</strong>. The idea is that you give your dog 2 full seconds to comply before applying a quick, light pop on the leash. It's not a yank. It's a quick "hey, remember the rules?" moment.</p>

<p class="my-4">Use this sparingly and only once your dog truly understands the rules of the leash. If they don't understand the rules yet, a correction won't help - only more practice will.</p>

